1
00:00:00,292 --> 00:00:02,667
I felt fear and terror

2
00:00:02,667 --> 00:00:04,584
They brought me into the cell

3
00:00:05,500 --> 00:00:07,542
My mattress was here in this spot

4
00:00:07,584 --> 00:00:09,626
And we hung our clothes here in this place

5
00:00:14,083 --> 00:00:15,918
And I was alone

6
00:00:15,918 --> 00:00:19,209
But every day or two they brought someone

7
00:00:19,626 --> 00:00:22,709
He stayed here an hour or two, a day or two

8
00:00:22,834 --> 00:00:24,209
Then they transferred him

9
00:00:24,667 --> 00:00:25,834
I don’t know where they took him

10
00:00:26,083 --> 00:00:29,250
I was afraid to ask, I couldn’t because they listened to us

11
00:00:30,959 --> 00:00:33,834
They brought a Christian man named Edmond

12
00:00:35,167 --> 00:00:36,459
That was because he became Muslim

13
00:00:37,042 --> 00:00:39,792
They brought him and we didn’t know his story

14
00:00:40,209 --> 00:00:42,000
He stayed two nights with me, two days

15
00:00:43,042 --> 00:00:44,334
Then they took him away

16
00:00:44,542 --> 00:00:47,959
Interviewer: Where did Edmond sleep?
Witness: He slept in that corner

17
00:00:48,959 --> 00:00:52,959
When he was here we were afraid to talk to each other

18
00:00:53,667 --> 00:00:57,500
Afraid they’d hear us, because you couldn’t trust them

19
00:00:59,334 --> 00:01:01,334
Interviewer: Can you give me Edmond’s description?

20
00:01:01,375 --> 00:01:03,959
And how old was he? And why was he detained?

21
00:01:04,375 --> 00:01:06,042
I don’t know exactly

22
00:01:06,083 --> 00:01:07,918
He was someone who’d converted to Islam

23
00:01:08,500 --> 00:01:10,083
Edmond used to sleep in this place

24
00:01:10,959 --> 00:01:15,083
He was about 22 or 23, a young man

25
00:01:16,083 --> 00:01:20,459
Once I asked him, Where are you from?

26
00:01:20,542 --> 00:01:21,584
He said, From the Aden neighborhood

27
00:01:21,959 --> 00:01:25,209
I still remember he told me he lived in the Aden neighborhood

28
00:01:25,292 --> 00:01:28,209
Interviewer: Didn’t you ask him about his family and why he stayed here?

29
00:01:28,209 --> 00:01:29,667
His family had gone to Erbil

30
00:01:30,209 --> 00:01:32,167
Interviewer: Didn’t you ask him why he hadn’t gone with them?

31
00:01:33,417 --> 00:01:34,918
I couldn’t ask him these questions

32
00:01:35,334 --> 00:01:41,959
I was afraid he’d tell them I was asking

33
00:01:42,292 --> 00:01:46,918
Interviewer: The food they brought you and the Christian who became Muslim

34
00:01:47,125 --> 00:01:49,542
Was it in one dish or did each of you have his own?

35
00:01:49,542 --> 00:01:50,792
No, each of us had his own dish

36
00:01:51,834 --> 00:01:54,542
They brought us <i>sammoun</i> [bread roll] and <i>tahini</i> too

37
00:01:55,292 --> 00:01:58,876
And the food was ready on plastic plates

38
00:01:59,292 --> 00:02:03,959
Bread, broth, and a spoon with it, and we ate

39
00:02:04,584 --> 00:02:07,834
Interviewer: The people they brought for two or three hours then took out

40
00:02:07,834 --> 00:02:09,125
What were their charges exactly?

41
00:02:10,292 --> 00:02:12,209
One of them was because of cigarettes

42
00:02:12,250 --> 00:02:16,709
And one of them because of a satellite dish

43
00:02:17,542 --> 00:02:19,459
They had been charged with many things

44
00:02:21,375 --> 00:02:24,709
Interviewer: Did these prisoners sleep with you in this prison?

45
00:02:24,709 --> 00:02:31,584
Edmond and one or two others slept here, I think a day or two

46
00:02:32,292 --> 00:02:36,834
Most of the time those they brought stayed only a few hours

47
00:02:36,834 --> 00:02:38,209
At most until the evening

48
00:02:38,542 --> 00:02:41,209
Interviewer: You said you spent 28 days in this room

49
00:02:41,751 --> 00:02:45,834
Didn’t you think of sending a message with someone who went in and out

50
00:02:45,918 --> 00:02:49,334
To tell your family where you were?

51
00:02:49,334 --> 00:02:52,042
I was afraid to do that

52
00:02:52,417 --> 00:02:58,834
Afraid they would ask him, What did this prisoner say to you?

53
00:02:59,751 --> 00:03:02,209
That was fear and terror

54
00:03:02,250 --> 00:03:06,626
Interviewer: While you were here did a jailer come in and beat you?

55
00:03:06,667 --> 00:03:11,626
Or beat someone who stayed here for a while with you?

56
00:03:11,667 --> 00:03:13,167
Did torture happen in this place?

57
00:03:13,209 --> 00:03:14,209
No, not here

58
00:03:14,292 --> 00:03:20,959
But we heard screams from the yard when they flogged someone

59
00:03:21,042 --> 00:03:24,876
Interviewer: For relieving yourself, where were the toilets?

60
00:03:24,918 --> 00:03:29,626
They were there, when we wanted the toilet we called and knocked on the door

61
00:03:29,667 --> 00:03:31,584
Then the jailer came and took us

62
00:03:31,626 --> 00:03:33,209
We relieved ourselves then he brought us back here

63
00:03:33,250 --> 00:03:36,918
Interviewer: Was there a set time to go out or was it when you needed to?

64
00:03:37,542 --> 00:03:40,083
No, they knew I was a bit sick

65
00:03:41,709 --> 00:03:44,083
So they let me go whenever I needed

66
00:03:44,959 --> 00:03:46,167
They told me, Knock on the door

67
00:03:46,209 --> 00:03:50,459
The jailer was there, he’d take us, we relieved ourselves, washed, then came back

68
00:03:51,167 --> 00:03:53,709
Interviewer: Did something happen while you were here for 28 days?

69
00:03:53,751 --> 00:03:57,918
With a jailer, a prisoner, or someone who came and left?

70
00:03:59,751 --> 00:04:01,959
Just that man named Edmond

71
00:04:02,417 --> 00:04:03,584
I was afraid to ask him

72
00:04:04,000 --> 00:04:08,334
We were afraid because the jailer outside might hear us

73
00:04:09,375 --> 00:04:10,751
One of the ISIS members

74
00:04:11,292 --> 00:04:13,626
We feared he’d hear us talking and shout at us

75
00:04:14,876 --> 00:04:17,250
Interviewer: The people they brought in temporarily then took out

76
00:04:17,542 --> 00:04:20,250
Did any of them ask why you were here?

77
00:04:20,292 --> 00:04:23,083
Yes, they asked me and I told them I was here because of medicine

78
00:04:24,709 --> 00:04:27,459
They asked, What was your charge?

79
00:04:27,500 --> 00:04:31,334
I said they brought me because of medicine, and my stay here dragged on

80
00:04:32,959 --> 00:04:35,542
Interviewer: Was this place furnished?

81
00:04:35,876 --> 00:04:38,667
Was there a carpet?

82
00:04:38,709 --> 00:04:40,167
Yes, in the middle

83
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:42,459
A nylon mat

84
00:04:43,417 --> 00:04:45,209
Here was my mattress, and a hanger

85
00:04:45,876 --> 00:04:48,626
And whoever came brought his own mattress

86
00:04:49,500 --> 00:04:52,959
Interviewer: You mean the temporary one brought his own mattress?
Witness: Yes

87
00:04:53,042 --> 00:04:54,709
Interviewer: And when he left, did they take it?

88
00:04:54,751 --> 00:04:55,918
No, he took it with him

89
00:04:56,626 --> 00:05:00,959
Interviewer: Do you think there were prisoners in those other rooms?

90
00:05:01,167 --> 00:05:02,334
And did you hear them?

91
00:05:02,375 --> 00:05:04,375
Yes, in that room there were prisoners

92
00:05:04,459 --> 00:05:05,792
But I don’t know what kind

93
00:05:05,876 --> 00:05:07,542
Interviewer: When you went to the bathroom

94
00:05:08,334 --> 00:05:12,042
Did you see other prisoners going at the same time?

95
00:05:12,083 --> 00:05:14,709
No, they never let one meet another

96
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:18,542
Interviewer: Do you remember how many jailers stood at the door?

97
00:05:18,792 --> 00:05:20,417
One stood here on duty

98
00:05:21,125 --> 00:05:23,167
Interviewer: You mean they rotated?
Witness: Yes

99
00:05:23,417 --> 00:05:25,667
Each one took over for two or three hours

100
00:05:25,834 --> 00:05:31,042
Interviewer: Do you remember the name of one of the jailers?

101
00:05:32,709 --> 00:05:35,000
Abu Hafsa, we called him that

102
00:05:35,042 --> 00:05:36,626
Interviewer: Who was Abu Hafsa?

103
00:05:36,834 --> 00:05:43,417
Abu Hafsa was from al-Hadar

104
00:05:43,459 --> 00:05:47,083
Interviewer: From Tikrit?
Witness: Yes, from Tikrit, from al-Hadar

105
00:05:47,834 --> 00:05:50,083
They called him Abu Hafsa, but I didn’t know his real name

106
00:05:50,125 --> 00:05:53,209
Because Abu Hafsa was a nom de guerre

107
00:05:54,918 --> 00:05:57,918
Interviewer: What did you talk about, did you ask him for anything?

108
00:05:57,959 --> 00:06:01,584
No, I just asked him to bring me water, for example

109
00:06:01,626 --> 00:06:03,042
Or to buy me something from outside

110
00:06:03,083 --> 00:06:05,417
Sometimes I gave him money

111
00:06:05,959 --> 00:06:10,083
So he could go buy what I wanted from the grocery in the street

112
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:13,709
Interviewer: So he could deal with you if you gave him money?

113
00:06:13,792 --> 00:06:15,959
Yes, they bought me what I wanted

114
00:06:15,959 --> 00:06:18,083
Interviewer: Did the money stay with you or was it in custody?

115
00:06:18,834 --> 00:06:20,834
No, the money was in my pocket

116
00:06:21,751 --> 00:06:23,959
My ID card and watch were in custody

117
00:06:23,959 --> 00:06:25,667
Interviewer: So they took your ID and watch?

118
00:06:25,709 --> 00:06:26,959
Yes, only those, the money stayed with me

119
00:06:27,667 --> 00:06:29,500
Interviewer: Was it normal for them to take money and buy things for you?

120
00:06:29,500 --> 00:06:30,709
Yes, and he gave me the change

121
00:06:30,751 --> 00:06:34,584
Interviewer: Did he take anything in return?
Witness: No

122
00:06:34,918 --> 00:06:37,500
Interviewer: Didn’t he take bribes or anything?
Witness: No, he didn’t

123
00:06:39,250 --> 00:06:40,834
Interviewer: How long did you stay in this room?

124
00:06:41,125 --> 00:06:42,209
28 days

125
00:06:42,709 --> 00:06:47,083
Interviewer: Are these windows the same and in this state?

126
00:06:47,167 --> 00:06:49,751
Yes, they had glass panels

127
00:06:50,792 --> 00:06:53,375
And were covered with metal from outside

128
00:06:54,292 --> 00:06:56,500
Interviewer: Were there cameras pointed at you?

129
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,417
No, there weren’t any cameras

130
00:06:58,459 --> 00:07:01,209
There was this fan, it’s still here now

131
00:07:02,417 --> 00:07:03,459
And two light bulbs

132
00:07:05,459 --> 00:07:08,709
Interviewer: Wasn’t there one of their flags on the walls?

133
00:07:08,709 --> 00:07:10,167
Yes, there was a flag here

134
00:07:11,042 --> 00:07:14,500
Interviewer: Did they use a screen to show their videos?

135
00:07:14,542 --> 00:07:16,542
No, the screen was downstairs

136
00:07:17,334 --> 00:07:19,083
Interviewer: Here there wasn’t one?
Witness: No, there wasn’t
